SIMPLE: materialistical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Materialistical
<hw>Ma*te`ri*al*is"tic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Of or pertaining to materialism or materialists; of the nature of
materialism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But to me his very spiritualism seemed more
<qex>materialistic</qex> than his physics.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Primarily concerned with material objects and
worldly activities, as contrasted with spiritual, moral or philosophical
concerns; especially, concerned primarily with gaining money and the
things that money can buy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Materiality</ent>⟦br⟧
